column3: (file format explainer)->
column4:
Localization files are formatted like CSV so they can be easily edited,
however formatting has strict rules for easy parsing. Most of these rules
are already handled by Excel / Libre / etc., so you don't have to worry
about them in normal usage. However, if your localization file seems to
be corrupted, these rules may be helpful for debugging purposes...
- The first 4 rows can be arbitrarily long
  - The first cell of first row is used to store this block of instruction
    text
  - The first 3 cells of the fourth row is used as headers
  - All other cells in the first and fourth rows are ignored
  - Columns in the second row alternate between property and value (ex.
    ' foo | 1 | bar | 3.5 | ... '
    - Any whitespaces before and after the property name are ignored
  - Columns in the third row are exclusively comments for properties in the
    second row
- Every following line can include any number of cells, but only the
  first four will be parsed (you can use the rest as comments if needed)
  - The fourth column is an optional metadata column

column3: NonDialogueFontScale

column1: Set to 1 allow the parser to read this file, otherwise it will be skipped and the default English localization will be used as fallback
column3: Float value that scales font size of all non-dialogue text, 1.0 for full size.
column5: Float value that scales font size of all dialogue text, 1.0 for full size.
column7: The author(s) of this file, will appear in credits

column2: Hey! Do you work here?

column3: MRI雇我们修好这座桥.我们需要一些[铁轨]和[矿车].

column3: 不过,我们的建材只够凑出其中的一个.

column3: 你能帮我找到一个[铁轨]或者一个[矿车]吗?另外一个我们自己可以搞定.

column3: 如果你能找到一个[矿车],他能给你一些回报.

column2: Nice, we can fix the bridge!
column3: 漂亮,我们能开工了!

column2: If you bring us a Minecart I can still try and get you that extra reward.

column2: And for your extra reward... I thought I might upgrade your new shoes!

column3: 你现在应该能跑的更快了.

column3: 为什么所有的电脑都朝[下]放着?

column2: Did you just-
column3: 你是不是刚才...

column3: 我刚刚还看着的!哦不...

column2: No no no no no no
column3: 不不不不不不!

column2: Everything's stuck now!

column2: Some archeologist from the other continent mentioned <#ff9040>A Scroll</color>.
column3: 另一个大陆来的一个考古学家向我提起 <#ff9040>一张卷轴</color>.

column2: She was heading to the desert north of here, I would appreciate if you followed.
column3: 她正往北边的沙漠走.你能不能跟上她找一找?

column3: 卷轴!你找到了!

column2: Go on, use it. Fix this place up!

column2: Well, that's great news! Thanks for doing it so quick.
column3: 真是好消息!你真是很有行动力.

column2: I'll let the guys below know, they can open the door to the Rocket Factory.
column3: 我会让伙计们知道的,他们会打开火箭工厂的大门.

column2: Nice! Everything is fixed now!

column2: If you want to fix the rest of the jungle, you should really go to the desert though.

column2: Some archeologist mentioned <#ff9040>A Scroll</color>, some super powerful artifact.

column2: I'll let the folks at the Rocket Factory know, the door should be open.

column2: Did you know we get free healthcare after our 365th day of working?

column2: Sorry pal... the Rocket Factory is closed until this rail line is permanently fixed.

column2: The rail line's fixed? Head on into the Rocket Factory then!
